   <RulePackDef>
    <defName>MR_Description_Schematic</defName>
    <include>
      <li>ArtDescriptionUtility_Global</li>
    </include>
    <rulePack>
      <rulesStrings>

        <li>desc->"......So, I'm sure you've all heard it at least once. The incubators currently in use are also widely known by the slang term 'Placenta.' And the shock I received when I was told about an apparatus of the same name, 'Placenta,' in a frontier household during this recent exchange meeting, stems from that very fact. They were extracting the literal 'placenta' of some animal to use as a cultivation device when handling genetic material. Aside from that fact, its principles, structure, and method of use were almost identical to the incubators we use today. Should this be considered a sort of parallel discovery? Perhaps our organic research technology also originated in the same way. The slang term 'Placenta' might be the remaining evidence of that. The excitement still hasn't worn off. This place is a continuous series of new discoveries, day after day. Once this exchange meeting is over, I can't wait to tell you all in person what I couldn't fully convey in this letter.\n\nP.S.: I managed to obtain a piece of the placenta tissue by asking the folks here! Don't you think it might help in materializing the design for that Gene Sculptor I mentioned before?"</li>

      </rulesStrings>
    </rulePack>
  </RulePackDef>

